<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>CAB: 5000i AND 9000i CONVENTIONAL - REMOVE - Remove REAR WINDOW GLASS AND WEATHER SEAL (EXCEPT SLEEPER
        MODELS)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Remove REAR WINDOW GLASS AND WEATHER SEAL (EXCEPT SLEEPER MODELS)</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1602114">Figure 14</hotlnk>
            for Items in parentheses.
        </para>
        <para>A one piece weather seal (Item 1) secures the rear window glass (Item 2) to the cab. The weather seal is
            molded to fit tightly over a flange at the edge of the window opening so it secures the glass in the window
            opening.
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Because old weather seals are likely to be damaged, always install a new seal when replacing the
                    glass.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Use only heat treated glass (AS-2 per ANSI Z26.1-Latest revision).</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">For easy removal of weather seal (Item 1) and rear window glass (Item 2), cut away the
                portion of weather seal that fits around window flange.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove rear window and remaining weather seal from window flange.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1602114" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602114.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 14. Rear Window Glass</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. WEATHER SEAL</callout1>
                <callout1>2. REAR WINDOW GLASS</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
